      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: cover cron setup watchdog timeout retries",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nMemory Cleanup Daily failed before its payload ran because the isolated cron runner setup exceeded the runner-start watchdog and returned `cron: isolated agent setup timed out before runner start`. That was a pre-run infrastructure/setup failure, not a memory-cleanup payload defect. The cron was repaired operationally by rerunning the job after setup capacity recovered; the scheduler now records `lastRunStatus: ok`, `lastStatus: ok`, and `consecutiveErrors: 0`.\n\nDuring RCA, the exact production `timed out before runner start` wording was confirmed to be timeout-retryable in current source because the classifier already matches `timed out`. The real code gap found in the same setup-watchdog family was the sibling wording `cron: isolated agent setup stalled before runner start`, which did not match the existing `stalled before execution start` phrase and would not be retried as a timeout.\n\n## Fix\nKeep the successful cron repair as the DoD proof, and harden the cron timeout classifier for the sibling runner-start setup stall wording. `src/cron/retry-hint.ts` now names the timeout pattern and explicitly matches `isolated agent setup stalled before runner start`, while preserving the existing `timeout`, `timed out`, `stalled before execution start`, and `etimedout` behavior.\n\n## Sibling Occurrences\nSearched `src/cron` for `TRANSIENT_PATTERNS`, `resolveCronExecutionRetryHint`, `timed out before runner start`, `stalled before execution start`, and setup/pre-execution watchdog wording. The exact production timeout wording is already covered by `timed out`; this PR covers the uncovered sibling setup-stall wording in the same runner-start failure class.\n\n## Evidence\n- RED -> GREEN test added: `src/cron/retry-hint.test.ts` asserts `cron: isolated agent setup stalled before runner start` classifies as `{ retryable: true, category: \"timeout\" }`.\n- RED proof for the changed behavior: direct regex check of the old source pattern returned `oldMatches=false` and the new pattern returned `newMatches=true` for `cron: isolated agent setup stalled before runner start`.\n- GREEN: `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/cron/retry-hint.test.ts src/cron/retry-hint.ts` passed.\n- Attempted GREEN: `pnpm exec vitest run src/cron/retry-hint.test.ts src/cron/service/timer.regression.test.ts --maxWorkers=1` and then the focused `pnpm exec vitest run src/cron/retry-hint.test.ts --maxWorkers=1`; both hung in Rolldown plugin timing/build output and were terminated without test failures. Prior run before this PR-body correction had passed the same cron test set.\n- Cron DoD proof: `openclaw cron get 83b82e1a-9e7b-4331-97c9-2190b909cb59` reports `lastRunStatus: ok`, `lastStatus: ok`, `consecutiveErrors: 0`, `lastDeliveryStatus: delivered`, and `enabled: true`.\n",
        "branch": "fix/cron-setup-watchdog-timeout-retry",
